description:
&lt;p&gt;Lincoln Clinical Engineering has a vacancy for a Support Assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post involves working as part of a busy team that provides a clinical support service that includes service, calibration and repair of electronic medical devices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Engineering at Lincoln is a lively, friendly department supporting thousands of medical devices for Lincoln County Hospital and other community health locations in the area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unlike many &#39;administration&#39; roles, this role is a mix of administration and practical work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a busy role supporting the Clinical Engineering team by:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helping manage the response desk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Triaging and resolving basic medical equipment problems on devices that comes to the department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring that purchase orders are processed efficiently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sending parcels to manufacturers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Helping with stock control and general administration duties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication skills, a good telephone manner, a methodical approach and word processing/IT skills are essential. Candidates must be fit enough to be able to manual handle the deliveries of equipment and spare parts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally, candidates will have previous administration experience and have practical skills. Training on our systems and processes will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum entry qualification is 4 GCE’s (or equivalent) at Grade C or above including English and Mathematics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or to arrange an informal visit please contact Dr Chris Hacking, Head of Clinical Engineering, Tel: 01522 573656 or Ela Bardan, Deputy Head of Clinical Engineering, Lincoln Tel. 01522 573664&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please quote job reference number when applying.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not re-apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
